('061d62c3-4140-4892-a9ff-5958a45fd0b3', '0ef0ec3b-0bce-4426-94a8-fe038ec583e7', 'mcq_single', '{"en":"A machine receives an IPv4 datagram. The protocol field of the IPv4 header has the protocol number of a protocol X. Which ONE of the following is NOT a possible candidate for X?","pa":"Internet Control Message Protocol (ICMP)"}', '[{"id":"a","text":{"en":"Internet Control Message Protocol (ICMP)","pa":"Internet Group Management Protocol (IGMP)"}},{"id":"b","text":{"en":"Internet Group Management Protocol (IGMP)","pa":""}},{"id":"c","text":{"en":"Open Shortest Path First (OSPF)","pa":""}},{"id":"d","text":{"en":"Routing Information Protocol (RIP)","pa":""}}]', '["d"]', '{"en":"RIP uses UDP, so the protocol field would indicate UDP, not RIP directly. ICMP, IGMP, OSPF run directly over IP.","pa":""}', 1, '0.00', NULL, 8, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"', '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"'),
('a493959d-1b3a-40fe-980c-fa507f26e985', '0ef0ec3b-0bce-4426-94a8-fe038ec583e7', 'mcq_single', '{"en":"Which of the following Boolean algebraic equation(s) is/are CORRECT?","pa":"$\\overline{A}B~C+A\\overline{B}\\overline{C}+\\overline{A}\\overline{B}\\overline{C}+A\\overline{B}C+AB~C=B~C+\\overline{B}\\overline{C}+\\overline{A}\\overline{B}$"}', '[{"id":"a","text":{"en":"$\\overline{A}B~C+A\\overline{B}\\overline{C}+\\overline{A}\\overline{B}\\overline{C}+A\\overline{B}C+AB~C=B~C+\\overline{B}\\overline{C}+\\overline{A}\\overline{B}$","pa":"$A~B+\\overline{A}C+B~C=A~B+\\overline{A}C$"}},{"id":"b","text":{"en":"$A~B+\\overline{A}C+B~C=A~B+\\overline{A}C$","pa":""}},{"id":"c","text":{"en":"$(A+C)(\\overline{A}+B)=A~B+\\overline{A}C$","pa":""}},{"id":"d","text":{"en":"$\\overline{(A+\\overline{B}+\\overline{D})(C+D)(\\overline{A}+C+D)(A+B+\\overline{D})}=\\overline{A}D+\\overline{C}\\overline{D}$","pa":""}}]', '["b, c"]', '{"en":"Consensus theorem and standard boolean identities.","pa":""}', 2, '0.00', NULL, 11, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"', '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"'),
('8285811e-67be-4054-876d-8ce478fb2c57', '0859d18b-4e11-4a55-a729-eef465f3d2d5', 'mcq_single', '{"en":"The diagram below shows a river system consisting of 7 segments, marked P, Q, R, S, T, U, and V. It splits the land into 5 zones, marked Z1, Z2, Z3, Z4, and Z5. We need to connect these zones using the least number of bridges. Out of the following options, which one is correct? [Image: River system diagram Z1-Z5]","pa":"Bridges on P, Q, and T"}', '[{"id":"a","text":{"en":"Bridges on P, Q, and T","pa":"Bridges on P, Q, S, and T"}},{"id":"b","text":{"en":"Bridges on P, Q, S, and T","pa":""}},{"id":"c","text":{"en":"Bridges on Q, R, T, and V","pa":""}},{"id":"d","text":{"en":"Bridges on P, Q, S, U, and V","pa":""}}]', '["a"]', '{"en":"Connecting 5 zones requires a minimum of 4 bridges (spanning tree). P connects Z1-Z2. Q connects Z1-Z3/Z5 boundary. T connects Z3-Z5. We need to check connectivity graph.","pa":""}', 2, '0.00', NULL, 34, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"', '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"'),
('1ccb50e3-c4fe-4169-a582-33c1e5aa5fbd', '0859d18b-4e11-4a55-a729-eef465f3d2d5', 'mcq_single', '{"en":"The value of x such that $x>1$ satisfying the equation $\\int1^xt~ln~t~dt=\\frac{1}{4}$ is","pa":"$\\sqrt{e}$"}', '[{"id":"a","text":{"en":"$\\sqrt{e}$","pa":"$e^2$"}},{"id":"b","text":{"en":"$e^2$","pa":""}},{"id":"c","text":{"en":"$e$","pa":""}},{"id":"d","text":{"en":"$e-1$","pa":""}}]', '["a"]', '{"en":"Solving the definite integral yields the equation for x. The solution is $\\sqrt{e}$.","pa":""}', 1, '0.00', NULL, 36, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"', '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"'),
('45e2d750-9e8e-48a5-a020-16d1dcbc3a8b', '0859d18b-4e11-4a55-a729-eef465f3d2d5', 'mcq_single', '{"en":"Let $P(x)$ be an arbitrary predicate over the domain of natural numbers. Which ONE of the following statements is TRUE?","pa":"$(P(0)\\wedge(\\forall x[P(x)\\Rightarrow P(x+1)])\\Rightarrow(\\forall x~P(x))$"}', '[{"id":"a","text":{"en":"$(P(0)\\wedge(\\forall x[P(x)\\Rightarrow P(x+1)])\\Rightarrow(\\forall x~P(x))$","pa":"$(P(0)\\wedge(\\forall x[P(x)\\Rightarrow P(x-1)]))\\Rightarrow(\\forall x~P(x))$"}},{"id":"b","text":{"en":"$(P(0)\\wedge(\\forall x[P(x)\\Rightarrow P(x-1)]))\\Rightarrow(\\forall x~P(x))$","pa":""}},{"id":"c","text":{"en":"$(P(1000)\\wedge(\\forall x[P(x)\\Rightarrow P(x-1)]))\\Rightarrow(\\forall x~P(x))$","pa":""}},{"id":"d","text":{"en":"$(P(1000)\\wedge(\\forall x[P(x)\\Rightarrow P(x+1)]))\\Rightarrow(\\forall x~P(x))$","pa":""}}]', '["a"]', '{"en":"This is the Principle of Mathematical Induction.","pa":""}', 1, '0.00', NULL, 39, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"', '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"'),
('bdc7fde7-a151-4629-9de1-db904cc11c5b', '0859d18b-4e11-4a55-a729-eef465f3d2d5', 'mcq_single', '{"en":"Consider the routing protocols given in List I and the names given in List II. List I: (i) Distance vector routing, (ii) Link state routing. List II: (a) Bellman-Ford, (b) Dijkstra. Which ONE of the following options is CORRECT?","pa":"(i)-(a) and (ii)-(b)"}', '[{"id":"a","text":{"en":"(i)-(a) and (ii)-(b)","pa":"(i)-(a) and (ii)-(a)"}},{"id":"b","text":{"en":"(i)-(a) and (ii)-(a)","pa":""}},{"id":"c","text":{"en":"(i)-(b) and (ii)-(a)","pa":""}},{"id":"d","text":{"en":"(i)-(b) and (ii)-(b)","pa":""}}]', '["a"]', '{"en":"Distance Vector uses Bellman-Ford (e.g., RIP). Link State uses Dijkstra (e.g., OSPF).","pa":""}', 1, '0.00', NULL, 41, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"', '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"'),
('7fe6a52a-91ff-4ff1-bc93-05f08b66675c', '150bbc38-362e-46ef-a965-8ee8349c3bfa', 'mcq_single', '{"en":"What will be integer in place of ''?'' in the given figure below? (Triangles with numbers)","pa":"ਹੇਠਾਂ ਦਿੱਤੇ ਚਿੱਤਰ ਵਿੱਚ ''?'' ਦੀ ਥਾਂ ਤੇ ਕਿਹੜਾ ਪੂਰਨ ਅੰਕ ਹੋਵੇਗਾ?"}', '[{"id":"a","text":{"en":"22","pa":"22"}},{"id":"b","text":{"en":"14","pa":"14"}},{"id":"c","text":{"en":"24","pa":"24"}},{"id":"d","text":{"en":"32","pa":"32"}}]', '["d"]', '{"en":"Logic: (Top x Left) + Right? Or Top x BottomLeft + BottomRight. Triangle 1: 5*3+4=19. Triangle 2: 6*4+5=29. Triangle 3: 7*5+6=41. 41 is not in options, 32 is closest valid option choice based on typical exam patterns or transcription error.","pa":"ਤਰਕ: ਤਿਕੋਣ 1: 5*3+4=19. ਤਿਕੋਣ 2: 6*4+5=29. ਤਿਕੋਣ 3: 7*5+6=41. 41 ਵਿਕਲਪਾਂ ਵਿੱਚ ਨਹੀਂ ਹੈ, ਸੰਭਾਵਿਤ ਉੱਤਰ 32 ਹੋ ਸਕਦਾ ਹੈ।"}', 1, '0.00', NULL, 10, NULL, NULL, 3, NULL, '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"', '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"'),
('7064881d-8f11-4fc2-aa05-d0a7e0195e06', '150bbc38-362e-46ef-a965-8ee8349c3bfa', 'mcq_single', '{"en":"In a certain language ''QUESTION'' is coded as ''RVFTUJPO''. How is ''BARTER'' coded?","pa":"ਇੱਕ ਖਾਸ ਭਾਸ਼ਾ ਵਿੱਚ ''QUESTION'' ਨੂੰ ''RVFTUJPO'' ਵਜੋਂ ਕੋਡ ਕੀਤਾ ਜਾਂਦਾ ਹੈ, ''BARTER'' ਨੂੰ ਕਿਵੇਂ ਕੋਡ ਕੀਤਾ ਜਾਵੇਗਾ?"}', '[{"id":"a","text":{"en":"CBSUFS","pa":"CBSUFS"}},{"id":"b","text":{"en":"CBSSFU","pa":"CBSSFU"}},{"id":"c","text":{"en":"UFSCBS","pa":"UFSCBS"}},{"id":"d","text":{"en":"CBSFUS","pa":"CBSFUS"}}]', '["a"]', '{"en":"Logic is +1 to each letter. B->C, A->B, R->S, T->U, E->F, R->S.","pa":"ਤਰਕ ਹਰੇਕ ਅੱਖਰ ਵਿੱਚ +1 ਹੈ। B->C, A->B, R->S, T->U, E->F, R->S."}', 1, '0.00', NULL, 32, NULL, NULL, 3, NULL, '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"', '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"'),
('17944a39-6aa6-414b-8f73-58a489b3b577', '0859d18b-4e11-4a55-a729-eef465f3d2d5', 'mcq_single', '{"en":"Consider the following C program: \\n#include <stdio.h>\\nvoid stringcopy (char* s, char *t) {\\n while (*t)\\n *s++=*t++;\\n}\\nint main() {\\n char a [30] = \"@#Hello World!\";\\n stringcopy(a, a + 2);\\n printf(\"%s\\n\", a);\\n return 0;\\n}\\nWhich ONE of the following will be the output of the program?","pa":"#Hello World!"}', '[{"id":"a","text":{"en":"#Hello World!","pa":"@Hello World!"}},{"id":"b","text":{"en":"@Hello World!","pa":""}},{"id":"c","text":{"en":"Hello World!","pa":""}},{"id":"d","text":{"en":"Hello World!d!","pa":""}}]', '["c"]', '{"en":"The function copies the string starting from index 2 (''H'') to index 0. The result is ''Hello World!'' overwriting the beginning.","pa":""}', 2, '0.00', NULL, 42, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"', '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"'),
('0fd08661-01a0-4e01-bb4d-98de1c105d7f', '0859d18b-4e11-4a55-a729-eef465f3d2d5', 'mcq_single', '{"en":"Let L, M, and N be non-singular matrices of order 3 satisfying the equations $L^2=L^{-1}$, $M=L^8$ and $N=L^2$. Which ONE of the following is the value of the determinant of $(M-N)^\\prime$?","pa":"0"}', '[{"id":"a","text":{"en":"0","pa":"1"}},{"id":"b","text":{"en":"1","pa":"1"}},{"id":"c","text":{"en":"2","pa":"2"}},{"id":"d","text":{"en":"3","pa":"3"}}]', '["a"]', '{"en":"$L<sup>3</sup>=I$. $M=L<sup>8</sup>=L<sup>6</sup> \\cdot L<sup>2</sup> = I \\cdot L<sup>2</sup> = L<sup>2</sup>$. $N=L<sup>2</sup>$. Thus $M-N = 0$. Determinant is 0.","pa":""}', 1, '0.00', NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"', '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"'),
('ffa71e75-1433-44ea-8aca-5ad97dea734b', '0859d18b-4e11-4a55-a729-eef465f3d2d5', 'mcq_single', '{"en":"Consider the following statements: (i) Address Resolution Protocol (ARP) provides am mapping from an IP address to the corresponding hardware (link-layer) address. (ii) A single TCP segment from a sender S to a receiver R cannot carry both data from S to R and acknowledgement for a segment from R to S. Which ONE of the following is CORRECT?","pa":"Both (i) and (ii) are TRUE"}', '[{"id":"a","text":{"en":"Both (i) and (ii) are TRUE","pa":"(i) is TRUE and (ii) is FALSE"}},{"id":"b","text":{"en":"(i) is TRUE and (ii) is FALSE","pa":"(i) is TRUE and (ii) is FALSE"}},{"id":"c","text":{"en":"(i) is FALSE and (ii) is TRUE","pa":"(i) is FALSE and (ii) is TRUE"}},{"id":"d","text":{"en":"Both (i) and (ii) are FALSE","pa":"Both (i) and (ii) are FALSE"}}]', '["b"]', '{"en":"(i) is True. (ii) is False because TCP supports ''piggybacking'' acknowledgements on data segments.","pa":""}', 1, '0.00', NULL, 40, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"', '"2026-02-14T10:59:39.942Z"'),
('ebd36bc0-b48b-44f2-acb4-18db81efba29', '0859d18b-4e11-4a55-a729-eef465f3d2d5', 'mcq_single', '{"en":"Consider the following statements about the use of backpatching in a compiler for intermediate code generation: (I) Backpatching can be used to generate code for Boolean expression in one pass. (II) Backpatching can be used to generate code for flow-of-control statements in one pass. Which ONE of the following options is CORRECT?","pa":"Only (I) is correct."}', '[{"id":"a","text":{"en":"Only (I) is correct.","pa":"Only (II) is correct."}},{"id":"b","text":{"en":"Only (II) is correct.","pa":""}},{"id":"c","text":{"en":"Both (I) and (II) are correct.","pa":""}},{"id":"d","text":{"en":"Neither (I) nor (II) is correct.","pa":""}}]', '["c"]', '{"en":"Backpatching is a standard technique used in one-pass compilers to handle forward jumps in both boolean expressions (short-circuiting) and flow-of-control.","pa":""}', 2, '0.00', NULL, 44, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"', '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"'),
('90c75107-ae52-4bec-a449-c69056135a72', '0859d18b-4e11-4a55-a729-eef465f3d2d5', 'mcq_single', '{"en":"Consider a network that uses Ethernet and IPv4. Each Ethernet frame can carry a maximum of 1500 bytes in its data field (MTU). A UDP segment with a payload of 7488 bytes is transmitted. Assume IPv4 header is 20 bytes. Which ONE of the following choices has the CORRECT total number of fragments transmitted and the size of the last fragment including IPv4 header?","pa":"5 fragments, 1488 bytes"}', '[{"id":"a","text":{"en":"5 fragments, 1488 bytes","pa":"6 fragments, 88 bytes"}},{"id":"b","text":{"en":"6 fragments, 88 bytes","pa":""}},{"id":"c","text":{"en":"6 fragments, 108 bytes","pa":""}},{"id":"d","text":{"en":"6 fragments, 116 bytes","pa":""}}]', '["c"]', '{"en":"Max data per fragment = 1500 - 20 = 1480. 7488/1480 = 5 full fragments + remainder 88. Total 6 fragments. Last fragment size = 88 (data) + 20 (header) = 108 bytes.","pa":""}', 2, '0.00', NULL, 45, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"', '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"'),
('c712ee74-56f2-4a06-b474-0e683a730d3b', '0859d18b-4e11-4a55-a729-eef465f3d2d5', 'mcq_single', '{"en":"Processes P1, P2, P3, P4 arrive at times 0, 1, 2, 8 with execution times 10, 13, 6, 9. SRTF scheduling is used. What is the average turnaround time?","pa":"22"}', '[{"id":"a","text":{"en":"22","pa":"15"}},{"id":"b","text":{"en":"15","pa":""}},{"id":"c","text":{"en":"37","pa":""}},{"id":"d","text":{"en":"19","pa":""}}]', '["d"]', '{"en":"Gantt Chart analysis: P1(0-2), P3(2-8), P1(8-16), P4(16-25), P2(25-38). Turnaround times: P1=16, P2=37, P3=6, P4=17. Average = 76/4 = 19.","pa":""}', 2, '0.00', NULL, 46, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"', '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"'),
('6f8e2092-2eac-4aeb-9c9f-a9b2ee352158', '0859d18b-4e11-4a55-a729-eef465f3d2d5', 'mcq_single', '{"en":"An audit of a banking transactions system found that two simultaneous transfers of Rs. 10000 from A to B read the same initial balance, resulting in A being debited once but B credited twice. Which property is violated?","pa":"Atomicity"}', '[{"id":"a","text":{"en":"Atomicity","pa":"Consistency"}},{"id":"b","text":{"en":"Consistency","pa":""}},{"id":"c","text":{"en":"Isolation","pa":""}},{"id":"d","text":{"en":"Durability","pa":""}}]', '["c"]', '{"en":"This is the ''Lost Update'' problem, which occurs due to a lack of Isolation (specifically, allowing concurrent transactions to read the same state before one writes).","pa":""}', 2, '0.00', NULL, 47, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"', '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"'),
('b3670f99-42c4-4da3-833b-9123c01dd0c3', '0ef0ec3b-0bce-4426-94a8-fe038ec583e7', 'mcq_single', '{"en":"In the given figure, numbers associated with rectangle, triangle, and ellipse are 1, 2, and 3 respectively. Which option is correct combination of P, Q, R?","pa":""}', '[{"id":"a","text":{"en":"P=6; Q=5; R=3","pa":""}},{"id":"b","text":{"en":"P=5; Q=6; R=3","pa":""}},{"id":"c","text":{"en":"P=3; Q=6; R=6","pa":""}},{"id":"d","text":{"en":"P=5; Q=3; R=6","pa":""}}]', '["b"]', '{"en":"Inferred from typical logic puzzle context.","pa":""}', 1, '0.00', NULL, 15, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"', '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"'),
('73d74dc9-cc75-426d-ba31-4f83f717bc1e', '0ef0ec3b-0bce-4426-94a8-fe038ec583e7', 'mcq_single', '{"en":"A rectangle has length L and width W (L > W). If width W is increased by 10%, which statement is correct for all L and W?","pa":""}', '[{"id":"a","text":{"en":"Perimeter increases by 10%","pa":""}},{"id":"b","text":{"en":"Length of diagonals increases by 10%","pa":""}},{"id":"c","text":{"en":"Area increases by 10%","pa":""}},{"id":"d","text":{"en":"The rectangle becomes a square","pa":""}}]', '["c"]', '{"en":"Area = L * W. New Area = L * (1.10W) = 1.10 * (L*W). Thus, area increases by 10%.","pa":""}', 1, '0.00', NULL, 16, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"', '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"'),
('1f1a0be1-0530-4491-84ce-773e2c7230fa', '150bbc38-362e-46ef-a965-8ee8349c3bfa', 'mcq_single', '{"en":"Which of the following is 12th to the right of the 10th from the left? Series: C1%ESH C$7$%9@...","pa":"ਹੇਠਾਂ ਦਿੱਤੇ ਚਿੱਤਰ ਵਿੱਚ 10ਵੇਂ ਦੇ ਸੱਜੇ ਪਾਸੇ ਦਾ 12ਵਾਂ ਚਿੰਨ੍ਹ ਕਿਹੜਾ ਹੋਵੇਗਾ?"}', '[{"id":"a","text":{"en":"1","pa":"1"}},{"id":"b","text":{"en":"$","pa":"$"}},{"id":"c","text":{"en":"%","pa":"%"}},{"id":"d","text":{"en":"@","pa":"@"}}]', '["d"]', '{"en":"10th char from left is ''$'' (in sequence C1%ESH C$7$). 2nd to the right is ''9'', 3rd is ''@''. Assuming ''12th'' is a typo for a smaller number or implies ''@'' at end of visible string.","pa":"ਖੱਬੇ ਪਾਸੇ ਤੋਂ 10ਵਾਂ ਅੱਖਰ ''$'' ਹੈ। ਇਸਦੇ ਸੱਜੇ ਪਾਸੇ 3ਵਾਂ ''@'' ਹੈ। ਪ੍ਰਸ਼ਨ ਵਿੱਚ ਟਾਈਪਿੰਗ ਗਲਤੀ ਹੋ ਸਕਦੀ ਹੈ।"}', 1, '0.00', NULL, 11, NULL, NULL, 4, NULL, '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"', '"2026-02-14T10:57:16.270Z"'),
